    <CompAttribute name="proformaLineDescriptions" id="f1667e62-6614-4fd1-b7be-050d058c054c">
        <type name="StringArray"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>
	// TFS 45953 Deleted code for deleted attribute



In the original design there was one cash payment for all pro forma payments, with the details of the individual charges stored in these three arrays:
proformaLineDescriptions (the invoice line description of each pro forma charge)
proformaLineQuantities (the quantity of each pro forma invoice line)
and proformaLineTotals (the value of each pro forma invoice line)

There is now one CM_CashPayment and one CM_ProformaDetails for each of the original pro forma invoice lines so
these should no longer be used.

As at August 2016 these are no longer maintained but are still read in CM_CashReceipt::getInvoiceStatsByILDSize to handle printing old receipts.
This code (which is the only usage other than the now-removed maintenance code) also gets the details from the CM_ProformaDetails if present.

NOTE that the old maintenance code is still in 841 SMAST if ever needed.</text>
    </CompAttribute>
